HEADWORD: Metecorn
<hw>Mete"corn`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A quantity of corn
formerly given by the lord to his customary tenants, as an encouragement
to, or reward for, labor and faithful service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Metely</ent>⟦br⟧
